No, seriously, is it enough?

32:04.593 --> 32:07.138
Because, look, I know this business.

32:07.162 --> 32:08.606
Perception is reality.

32:08.630 --> 32:10.775
- Yes.
- And if they think that Lucious did this,

32:10.799 --> 32:12.777
then Lucious did this.

32:12.801 --> 32:14.245
- I hear you, sis.
- WOMAN: Uh, Ms. Sims?

32:14.269 --> 32:15.547
I just need you to trust me.

32:15.571 --> 32:16.815
- Hi.
- (CHUCKLES)

32:16.839 --> 32:19.005
Let me do what I do.

32:21.944 --> 32:24.477
(CHURCH BELLS TOLLING)

32:38.760 --> 32:39.938
Wait.

32:39.962 --> 32:42.963
I need to see him one last time.

32:45.100 --> 32:47.078
Can, uh, we open the casket, please?

32:47.102 --> 32:49.135
Thank you.

33:05.721 --> 33:07.632
(SNIFFLES)

33:07.656 --> 33:10.824
My firstborn baby boy.

33:14.029 --> 33:16.140
(SIGHS SOFTLY)

33:16.164 --> 33:18.476
This is my music.

33:18.500 --> 33:23.103
You keep it... with you.

33:29.044 --> 33:31.711
♪ ♪

33:48.363 --> 33:51.162
- (DOORS CLOSE)
- THIRSTY: Are you kidding me?

33:51.163 --> 33:53.041
This is a funeral. The man's grieving.

33:53.065 --> 33:55.844
We understand that,
but we need to talk to him.

33:55.868 --> 33:57.379
Now.

33:57.403 --> 34:00.537
I'm very sorry for your loss.

34:06.512 --> 34:08.155
We both know that Damon Cross

34:08.156 --> 34:10.467
is a snake
that needs to be taken down.

34:10.492 --> 34:12.313
If you excuse us,
my client needs to bury his son.

34:12.313 --> 34:15.025
The thought of your wife
in the throes of passion,

34:15.050 --> 34:19.119
screaming Damon Cross's name,
that doesn't bother you at all?

34:20.722 --> 34:22.667
See this photo?

34:22.690 --> 34:26.804
This was taken long before
their business trip to Panama.

34:26.828 --> 34:29.896
Did your little Chocolate Chip
tell you that she knew him?

34:33.368 --> 34:36.880
As a matter of fact, she did.

34:36.905 --> 34:38.917
Did she also tell you
about all her little visits

34:38.940 --> 34:41.819
to his apartment while your son
was dying of cancer?

34:41.842 --> 34:44.522
What do you suppose
they were doing in there, huh?

34:44.545 --> 34:46.880
Relax, relax. It's gonna be okay.

34:48.116 --> 34:51.362
First you tried Thirsty,

34:51.386 --> 34:53.431
then you try and flip my wife.

34:53.455 --> 34:56.734
Then you come here the day
my son is being buried

34:56.757 --> 35:01.339
and try and make me betray
everything that matters to me

35:01.363 --> 35:03.274
just because you
and your little flunkies

35:03.298 --> 35:05.910
know how to play with Photoshop?

35:05.934 --> 35:07.600
Bitch, please.

35:12.207 --> 35:13.640
(PHONE CHIMES)

35:24.553 --> 35:26.586
(PHONES RINGING IN DISTANCE)

35:32.794 --> 35:35.373
To what do I owe the pleasure,
Mr. Cross?

35:35.397 --> 35:39.444
Well, the word on the streets is
you have political aspirations.

35:39.468 --> 35:41.212
I just so happen to have $20 million

35:41.236 --> 35:42.981
to throw into
the next governor's race,

35:43.005 --> 35:45.483
but for the right candidate.

35:45.507 --> 35:47.485
Are you the right candidate,
Ms. Conway?

35:47.509 --> 35:49.387
You're gonna have to offer
more than money

35:49.411 --> 35:51.489
to get me off your ass, Mr. Cross.

35:51.513 --> 35:54.225
Well, I can get you Lucious Lyon.

35:54.249 --> 35:57.717
Do you think you can get him
before he kills you?

35:59.654 --> 36:01.566
Beg your pardon?

36:01.590 --> 36:03.735
Well, I told him about
your obsession with his wife.

36:03.759 --> 36:05.103
Didn't go over too well.

36:05.127 --> 36:08.006
Turns out, he's obsessed
with her, too.

36:08.030 --> 36:11.175
You might've wanted me, but
he's the big flashy takedown.

36:11.199 --> 36:13.644
Exactly what you need
to make a name for yourself.

36:13.668 --> 36:15.702
I see where you're going.

36:17.806 --> 36:20.284
You want another
little nibble of the cookie.

36:20.308 --> 36:23.921
I get Lucious; you get his wife.

36:23.945 --> 36:26.624
I'll take Lucious now.

36:26.648 --> 36:28.848
Next year, the 20 mil.

36:42.927 --> 36:46.506
Um, girl, why you got me up in
here breathing in this asbestos?

36:46.530 --> 36:49.076
Because I heard you, sis,
about being tired

36:49.100 --> 36:50.844
of not getting credit for what you do,

36:50.868 --> 36:52.579
and because I share your pain.

36:52.603 --> 36:55.082
See, I thought
we should present the Lyons

36:55.106 --> 36:57.918
with a business plan
for our own imprint.

36:57.942 --> 37:01.188
Way we could make our own
decisions, sign our own artists.

37:01.212 --> 37:02.689
But if we have our own imprint,

37:02.713 --> 37:04.558
Lucious would still be
pulling the strings.

37:04.582 --> 37:06.560
If we had our own label,

37:06.584 --> 37:09.429
owned by women... us...

37:09.453 --> 37:12.199
run by women... us...

37:12.223 --> 37:14.935
for women... us.

37:14.959 --> 37:17.104
With what money?

37:17.128 --> 37:19.973
I spoke to my business manager
this morning,

37:19.997 --> 37:24.211
and I'm dumping my equity
in Empire, all of it.

37:24.235 --> 37:25.445
And if you do the same...

37:25.469 --> 37:27.147
The same?! Bitch, I ain't got it!

37:27.171 --> 37:29.149
It's 80/20. That's the split.

37:29.173 --> 37:32.152
80/20? Are you out your mind?

37:32.176 --> 37:35.555
Do you even know
how many record labels fail?

37:35.579 --> 37:38.392
Why would "us" do this?

37:38.416 --> 37:40.227
Because I believe in us.

37:40.251 --> 37:42.929
What we have together is real,

37:42.953 --> 37:46.800
but what we can do together is epic.

37:46.824 --> 37:49.403
- We could pull our own strings.
- Yeah.

37:49.427 --> 37:51.960
Finally get credit for what we do.

37:57.268 --> 37:58.645
30/70.

37:58.669 --> 38:01.782
(BOTH SCREAMING)

38:01.806 --> 38:05.619
Welcome to Bossy Records, girl.

38:05.643 --> 38:07.187
- Bossy? Bo... You sure?
- Yes, Bossy.

38:07.211 --> 38:08.622
What about The Shempire, huh?

38:08.646 --> 38:10.846
- GISELLE: Uh...
- BECKY: What about Okurrr?

38:14.719 --> 38:16.997
What are you doing, man?

38:17.021 --> 38:19.433
Taking care of my business.

38:19.457 --> 38:20.867
No, you're-you're being emotional.

38:20.891 --> 38:23.036
Okay, let's just,
let's just take it easy.

38:23.060 --> 38:25.305
Take it easy? I will take it easy

38:25.329 --> 38:28.308
when Damon Cross' ass
is six feet underground.

38:28.332 --> 38:30.043
- That's when I'll take it easy.
- Uh, look...

38:30.067 --> 38:31.611
He tried to take my wife!

38:31.635 --> 38:33.280
Wh-What, you think Conway
showed you those photos

38:33.304 --> 38:34.748
'cause she wanted to play
marriage counselor?

38:34.772 --> 38:37.217
Come on, she's just trying
to wind you up. Think about it.

38:37.241 --> 38:41.822
She is good at her damn job
'cause I'm wound up!

38:41.846 --> 38:43.724
Listen to me. My peoples
tell me Cross flipped.

38:43.748 --> 38:45.625
He's working with Conway.
He fed her enough lies

38:45.649 --> 38:47.894
so she could get a warrant
with your name on it.

38:47.918 --> 38:50.497
Yeah, well, don't you even
want to hear my plan?

38:50.521 --> 38:53.834
Okay, man. All right.
Tell me your plan.

38:53.858 --> 38:56.636
Plan is I go and finish him.

38:56.660 --> 38:58.538
Then I'm-a take off for a little bit

38:58.562 --> 39:00.640
until I find out
what Conway has on me,

39:00.664 --> 39:02.642
and then I'm gonna return.

39:02.666 --> 39:05.011
Well, Conway's plan is
to arrest you by noon,

39:05.035 --> 39:07.247
throw your ass in Rikers
where she can hold you

39:07.271 --> 39:08.749
for two years with no bail!

39:08.773 --> 39:11.885
But you go ahead, you go ahead
and waste time chasing Cross.

39:11.909 --> 39:13.942
You'll be playing yourself.

39:16.380 --> 39:18.413
Come on, man.

39:22.887 --> 39:24.831
Okay.

39:24.855 --> 39:26.989
We'll cross paths another day.

39:29.927 --> 39:34.908
Thirst, I built this empire
for my boys.

39:34.932 --> 39:39.346
Please make sure that they
look after it until I get back.

39:39.370 --> 39:41.748
Your boys are men now,

39:41.772 --> 39:44.439
and I will be there
whenever they need me.

39:52.650 --> 39:54.683
♪ ♪

40:06.096 --> 40:09.309
Come on, baby. It's about time.

40:09.333 --> 40:13.947
That damn U.S. attorney chick
is spreading all these lies,

40:13.971 --> 40:16.149
trying to pin me down on some stuff,

40:16.173 --> 40:18.585
so I figured we'd take off
for a little bit,

40:18.609 --> 40:21.543
and then, when things get better...

40:23.347 --> 40:26.259
Now-now-now, look.

40:26.283 --> 40:28.161
Baby, I know, I know.

40:28.185 --> 40:31.631
I know it's a lot,
but she is relentless.

40:31.655 --> 40:35.769
She has gone to manufacturing
pictures to try and look like

40:35.793 --> 40:37.804
you and Damon were sleeping together.

40:37.828 --> 40:39.306
You hear what I'm saying?

40:39.330 --> 40:41.675
I'm not leaving my son, Lucious.

40:41.699 --> 40:44.578
I'm not leaving my family again.

40:44.602 --> 40:46.346
Wait, wait, wait, no, no, no, no.

40:46.370 --> 40:48.415
No, you don't have to worry
about Andre.

40:48.439 --> 40:50.250
I talked to Teri.

40:50.274 --> 40:54.688
Teri promised me that she was
gonna look after him. Come on.

40:54.712 --> 40:58.491
You promised we would be better.
We ain't better, Lucious.

40:58.515 --> 41:01.761
Will you get... just get on
the damn helicopter.

41:01.785 --> 41:03.685
No, I'm not.

41:06.490 --> 41:08.657
Ride or die is over.

41:10.628 --> 41:13.540
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

41:13.564 --> 41:17.143
Back when I got out,

41:17.167 --> 41:19.613
I told you I wanted
half of my company.

41:19.637 --> 41:22.449
I gave you half of the company.

41:22.473 --> 41:24.351
But all I really wanted
was all of you.

41:24.375 --> 41:25.886
That's what you got
is all of me right now...

41:25.910 --> 41:28.154
You...

41:28.178 --> 41:32.058
you and Empire,
you're not good for me.

41:32.082 --> 41:33.793
Mm-mm.

41:33.817 --> 41:39.388
I will not sacrifice me
or my sons for you anymore.

41:42.660 --> 41:45.872
Baby, you... you love me.

41:45.896 --> 41:49.809
It's not enough, Lucious.
It's not enough, Lucious!

41:49.833 --> 41:52.479
It's not enough, okay?

41:52.503 --> 41:55.682
I can't trust you.

41:55.706 --> 41:59.052
Your lies, your s... blindsides.

41:59.076 --> 42:02.355
You hurt me too many times, okay?

42:02.379 --> 42:06.359
I got to put me first.
I got to put me first!

42:06.383 --> 42:08.395
- I got to put me first, Lucious!
- I-I understand that,

42:08.419 --> 42:11.064
and I promise you
I hear everything you're saying,

42:11.088 --> 42:13.266
and when we get to where we're
going, we're gonna talk about...

42:13.290 --> 42:15.568
- Damon Cross! Damon Cross!
- Wait, what...

42:15.592 --> 42:18.405
I slept with him, okay?
I slept with him.

42:18.429 --> 42:20.573
I said it.

42:20.597 --> 42:23.632
Do you still want me to get
on that helicopter with you?

42:25.903 --> 42:28.336
(CRYING SOFTLY)

42:29.940 --> 42:31.918
♪ Say that you don't want me ♪

42:31.942 --> 42:34.187
♪ Say that you don't need me ♪

42:34.211 --> 42:38.124
♪ Tell me I'm the fool ♪

42:38.148 --> 42:41.428
♪ Tell me you've been tortured,
tell me you've been beaten ♪

42:41.452 --> 42:44.564
♪ And what I've done to you ♪

42:44.588 --> 42:48.601
♪ And even if it doesn't matter ♪

42:48.625 --> 42:52.038
♪ Matter what's true, oh, no ♪

42:52.062 --> 42:56.076
♪ Say that you don't want me,
say that you don't need me ♪

42:56.100 --> 42:59.546
♪ Tell me I'm the fool ♪

42:59.570 --> 43:01.748
♪ Tell me that it's over ♪

43:01.772 --> 43:03.583
♪ Tell me that you mean it ♪

43:03.607 --> 43:06.886
♪ This time is true ♪

43:06.910 --> 43:11.291
♪ Tell me that I'm unknown ♪

43:11.315 --> 43:13.348
♪ To you ♪

